12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 342 of Title 66, unless there is
16 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. As used in this section:
18 1. “Branch line” means a secondary railroad track that branches
19 off from a main railroad line;
20 2. “Conductor” means a conductor, switchman, brakeman,
21 trainman, or fireman, who is licensed and certified by the Federal
22 Railroad Administration;
23 3. “Engineer” means an engineer who is licensed and certified
24 by the Federal Railroad Administration;
